    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6070b3bf_632adae9",
        "filename": "infra/bots/gen_tasks.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 251,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-23T15:06:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "/shrug. We are as specific as we can be for the GPU, so it seems odd to be generic for the CPU, particularly for Perf. We use the gen codename when we don\u0027t have a more specific name, e.g. IntelBayTrail for GPU and Haswell_GCE for CPU.",
      "parentUuid": "4b8759fd_2278bcbe",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 251,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 251,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "7f185552c7ced49bff82ba98a6dd081b10034b77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "13556ca1_487e4eac",
        "filename": "infra/bots/gen_tasks.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 251,
      "author": {
        "id": 5010
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-25T12:22:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In practice \"SandyBridge\" or \"IvyBridge\" is much more informative than model number.  That rarely matters, but we\u0027d have to look it up every time to the thing we care about, the processor family codename.",
      "parentUuid": "6070b3bf_632adae9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 251,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 251,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "7f185552c7ced49bff82ba98a6dd081b10034b77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88724081_56ca32d9",
        "filename": "infra/bots/gen_tasks.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 251,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-25T14:39:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The processor family is often what we\u0027re interested in, but I think we\u0027re also often interested in whether it supports SSE41, AVX, AVX2, AVX512, etc. The family isn\u0027t enough info to determine that, since often Pentiums and Celerons support fewer extensions than the other brands. E.g. these two are both Sandy Bridge but only one has AVX:\nhttps://ark.intel.com/products/53478/Intel-Core-i7-2960XM-Processor-Extreme-Edition-8M-Cache-up-to-3_70-GHz\nhttps://ark.intel.com/products/69360/Intel-Pentium-Processor-997-2M-Cache-1_60-GHz",
      "parentUuid": "13556ca1_487e4eac",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 251,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 251,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "7f185552c7ced49bff82ba98a6dd081b10034b77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2227e7a8_43e74486",
        "filename": "infra/bots/jobs.json",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 147,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-25T11:26:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is there a difference between Haswell on GCE and on desktop?  We already have GCE in the name.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 147,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 147,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "7f185552c7ced49bff82ba98a6dd081b10034b77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "80879010_5b247b75",
        "filename": "infra/bots/jobs.json",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 147,
      "author": {
        "id": 5010
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-25T12:22:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, not interestingly so.  I\u0027d prefer \"Haswell\" here.",
      "parentUuid": "2227e7a8_43e74486",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 147,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 147,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "7f185552c7ced49bff82ba98a6dd081b10034b77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "03cc27de_420a171c",
        "filename": "infra/bots/jobs.json",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 147,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-25T14:39:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "On GCE, the CPU is virtualized. We have no information on whether \"Haswell\" means the same thing on different VMs. It\u0027s possible that GCE reports the CPU is Haswell even if it\u0027s emulated on Sandy Bridge or Skylake (although I think that\u0027s unlikely).\n\nIn practice, my guess is that within a particular datacenter, all Haswell CPUs are identical, and the CPU platform reported by GCE reflects the physical CPU. I don\u0027t know how zones map to datacenters, though.\n\nAnyhoo, I\u0027ll remove GCE from the job name since it doesn\u0027t provide any new information.",
      "parentUuid": "80879010_5b247b75",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 147,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 147,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "7f185552c7ced49bff82ba98a6dd081b10034b77",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
